                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "W",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "82634878-faca-47c5-b8ff-c0c3bd335aae"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "339512c2ad774295930cb",
            "questionText": "A car battery has an electromotive force (EMF) of $!$12.6\\,\\text{V}$!$ and an internal resistance of $!$0.08\\,\\Omega$!$. When the headlights are turned on, the battery supplies a current of $!$10\\,\\text{A}$!$. Determine the power delivered to the headlights.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "cf49a455123b4d0b9ce38",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the voltage drop across the battery's internal resistance. To do this, identify the correct formula that relates voltage, current, and resistance.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "1c8e3997-e1d9-4422-aace-b2d82e6e249a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V = I \\times r$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V = \\frac{I}{r}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$V = I + r$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "5d663e7b6e6e4f119ee7b",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that we would calculate the voltage drop using the selected formula, compute the voltage drop by multiplying the battery current by its internal resistance (with current being 10 A and resistance 0.08 \u03a9). What is the computed drop in voltage?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "0.8"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "V",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "1c8e3997-e1d9-4422-aace-b2d82e6e249a"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "ab5fb902c8d04e1c9b515",
                    "stepText": "Now, determine the voltage across the headlights by subtracting the internal voltage drop from the battery EMF. Use the value of the EMF (12.6 V) and the calculated voltage drop from the previous step. What is the resulting voltage across the headlights?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "11.8"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "V",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "aa41a63a-b3d4-4ca2-87a2-640e15a9d86b"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "310b93ca8c5c4f759a33d",
                    "stepText": "Finally, calculate the power delivered to the headlights by multiplying the load voltage by the current flowing through them. With a current of 10 A and the computed load voltage, what is the resulting power?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
